  "issue_number": 1675,
  "issue_title": "feat(statements): add account statement vault",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\r\n- Add a web-only Account Statement Vault for uploading, storing, linking, reviewing, and deleting account statements.\r\n- Add account-level statement coverage and balance-based reconciliation flags so users can see which months are backed by actual statements and where Sure's balance history appears mismatched.\r\n- Keep V1 foundation-first: no transaction creation/update/import, no provider statement sync, no AI parsing requirement, and no public API/OpenAPI changes.\r\n\r\n## Feature overview\r\nThis adds the core Statement Vault domain surface around `AccountStatement`. Users can upload PDF, CSV, or XLSX statement files into a general unmatched inbox, or directly from an account's Statements tab. Sure stores the original file through ActiveStorage, records file metadata and checksums, detects conservative statement metadata where deterministic signals exist, suggests obvious account matches, and lets users manually link, unlink, reject, edit metadata, download, or delete statements.\r\n\r\nThe account Statements tab shows month-by-month coverage states: covered, missing, duplicate, ambiguous, and mismatched. Reconciliation V1 is intentionally review-oriented: it compares statement opening/closing balances and derived period movement against Sure balance history when enough metadata exists, flags mismatches, and never mutates transactions.\r\n\r\n## What changed\r\n- Added `AccountStatement` with family ownership, optional account linkage, suggested account linkage, ActiveStorage original-file attachment, metadata fields, parser confidence, match confidence, review status, sanitized parser output, MD5 checksum, and SHA-256 content digest.\r\n- Added secure upload preparation and validation for `.pdf`, `.csv`, and `.xlsx`, including extension + detected MIME checks, PDF magic-header checks, 25MB file limit, and duplicate detection with DB-level race protection.\r\n- Added deterministic metadata detection for filenames and sampled CSV headers/date rows while avoiding raw statement text or raw transaction rows in stored parser output.\r\n- Added deterministic account suggestions using institution/name/last-four/currency hints, with conservative manual review flows.\r\n- Added Statement Vault inbox UI under settings plus an account Statements tab with upload, coverage timeline, linked statement table, and reconciliation badges.\r\n- Added model/controller/ActiveStorage authorization so statement files remain family-scoped, linked statements follow account sharing, and unmatched statements require statement manager access.\r\n- Added database constraints and indexes for statement ownership, statuses, byte size, checksums, SHA-256 digest format, period lookup, and suggested-account review lookup.\r\n\r\n## Related prior work\r\nRelated: https://github.com/we-promise/sure/pull/1382\r\n\r\nThat earlier PR explored LLM-assisted PDF statement processing and reconciliation inside the PDF import flow. This PR does not merge that `PdfImport` job/UI behavior because V1 needs a smaller canonical foundation first: secure archival storage, account linking, deterministic metadata, coverage, and balance mismatch flags. AI/tool-calling and PDF transaction extraction can build on `AccountStatement` later as review-before-import suggestions, but they should not be required for the vault and should not silently create or update transactions.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\n- Keeps original source documents attached to account history instead of leaving statement evidence outside Sure.\r\n- Helps users answer whether every month has statement backing and whether Sure's balance history appears to line up with those statements.\r\n- Provides a stable local-upload foundation for later CSV/XLSX parsing, reviewed statement-to-transaction import, optional AI suggestions, and provider statement sync.\r\n- Reduces scope risk by shipping archive + coverage + mismatch detection before transaction-level reconciliation or automated imports.\r\n\r\n@jjmata please let me know your thoughts regarding this - happy to discuss if you disagree!\r\n\r\n## Screenshots\r\nCaptured locally with headless Chromium from the live devcontainer app. The files are in this Codex workspace and can be uploaded/attached when this draft is promoted for review:\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th>Account Statements Tab</th>\r\n    <th>Statement Vault Inbox</th>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>\r\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/25b24863-edf8-4f40-9f8d-8c0998967ab6\">\r\n        <img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/25b24863-edf8-4f40-9f8d-8c0998967ab6\" alt=\"Account Statements Tab\" width=\"360\" />\r\n      </a>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td>\r\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fd0dd4af-e9ef-4cef-8a70-f19fe17b22b6\">\r\n        <img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fd0dd4af-e9ef-4cef-8a70-f19fe17b22b6\" alt=\"Statement Vault Inbox\" width=\"360\" />\r\n      </a>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th>Unmatched Statement Suggestion</th>\r\n    <th>Mismatched Statement Detail</th>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>\r\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/efcbdd87-7cfc-4ada-847c-ea9794f5b74a\">\r\n        <img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/efcbdd87-7cfc-4ada-847c-ea9794f5b74a\" alt=\"Unmatched Statement Suggestion\" width=\"360\" />\r\n      </a>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td>\r\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4288eba5-cbb6-4bf9-9cce-f9195589fa19\">\r\n        <img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4288eba5-cbb6-4bf9-9cce-f9195589fa19\" alt=\"Mismatched Statement Detail\" width=\"360\" />\r\n      </a>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n- `docker compose -f .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml exec -T app bin/rails test test/models/account_statement_test.rb test/controllers/account_statements_controller_test.rb test/controllers/accounts_controller_test.rb`\r\n- `docker compose -f .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml exec -T app bin/rails test test/integration/active_storage_authorization_test.rb -n '/statement blob|linked statement|unmatched statement blob|orphaned statement|orphaned transaction|unauthenticated user/'`\r\n- `docker compose -f .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml exec -T app bin/rubocop app/models/account_statement.rb test/models/account_statement_test.rb db/migrate/20260505130000_harden_account_statements.rb db/migrate/20260505131000_validate_account_statement_constraints.rb`\r\n- `docker compose -f .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml exec -T app bundle exec erb_lint app/views/account_statements/index.html.erb app/views/account_statements/show.html.erb app/views/accounts/show/_statements.html.erb`\r\n- `docker compose -f .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml exec -T app bin/brakeman`\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\n- `coderabbit review --agent -t committed`\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- No public API endpoints were added.\r\n- No rswag/OpenAPI docs were changed.\r\n- No AI parsing was added.\r\n- No provider statement sync was added.\r\n- Statement uploads do not create, update, import, or reconcile transactions in V1.\r\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Statement upload & management (PDF/CSV/XLSX) with original-file download, inbox, monthly coverage grid and year filter; statements tab on accounts and Statement Vault in settings\n  * Detailed statement view: metadata editing, reconciliation summary, manual link/unlink/reject, and automatic account-matching suggestions with confidence scores\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Localized UI text for statements and tabs\n  * Stronger authorization for statement attachments\n  * Linked statements moved to inbox when an account is deleted\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Comprehensive model, controller and integration tests for statements\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
